Penguins, explained

> **1) What is a penguin?**  
A penguin is a glorious, flightless bird that is arguably the king of the seas.
All penguins are part of the family _Spheniscidae_, which is divided into 18
species, including the emperor penguin (_Aptenodytes forsteri_), the Galapagos
penguin (_Spheniscus mendiculus_), and the macaroni penguin (_Eudyptes
chrysolophus_).  
— [Penguins, explained — Vox](http://www.vox.com/2015/1/20/7861749/penguins-explained).

